Jun 14 2009 	Great Location Average Hotel	This is a budget hotel that is clean and in walking distance (20 min) to most of the sites in montreal. There is no parking in the hotel but I parked at the Library underground parking 10 mins away for $7 for 24 hrs (weekend rate). There is also complimentary continental breakfast. We had a single double bed room that was clean, shower / tv / wireless internet / AC work fine. The room comes with an ironing board and iron, a fridge is also in the room (but was not plugged in - you can plug it in if you want to use it). The hotel is in an old building but the neighborhood is quiet and we did not hear anything from the other rooms. Contrary to the other reviews we did not have any bed bugs in our bed, however there were some bums up the street when we were walking back at night time - but they did not bother us.Overall it is a budget hotel and if you don't mind it being a bit rough around the edges it's a good location for a budget price. I would recommend staying here if you are on a budget.	
