Jul 1 2006	Worst hotel in Montreal	Friday...First off, the hotel had lost our reservations that were made one year in advance and confirmed the week prior by Choice Hotels. The manager made no attempt to correct the situation and when I showed him my guarantee of a room by Choice Hotels and I asked him to call them immediately, he told me I could call them on my own phone, he would have not part in helping us. I insisted that he call (he did but practically threw the phone at me after dialling) and there were many worried looking customers waiting to hopefully check in. He told us he didn't have any rooms at all, and there were none to be found in the city that weekend. After my initial conversation with Choice Hotels, he miraculously found a room, with one bed for the 3 of us. That obviously wasn't an option, I had a guarantee for 2 double beds and 3 adults in one bed wouldn't work. He then completely ignored me and moved on to other people waiting. Now, I became very angry and I insisted once again that he call Choice Hotels and find us a room. He refused. He wouldn't allow me to use the hotel phone at first but then handed it to me and told me to call Choice Hotels, he wouldn't even dial the phone. After my 2nd conversation with a superivisor for the chain, the manager found us a room with 2 double beds. We had now lost an entire day, paid for, at the F1 race, which isn't refundable and very expensive.On to the room...air conditioning doesn't work and it's very hot that weekend. I called the desk and they said they would call a service technician to fix the air conditioning. No one came and we spent a sleepless night in a hot, loud room. We had the window open 2&quot; and there wasn't a screen so all the bugs cam in during the night. As well, the drunken tourists made noise all night outside of our room, on the street.Sauturday...I complained at the front desk about the air conditioning and was told no one would be comng to fix it. I didn't even get an &quot;I'm sorry&quot;. Another night of bugs, heat and loud noises.Sunday...No water pressure for showers and towels for 2 people despite the fact that on Friday I told them we'd need towels for 3 (paying for 3 people) and I had to search for a chambermaid each day to get extra towels. I went to the front desk to get the 3rd set of towels and didn't notice it but was handed a set of completely shredded towels that you wouldn't use to wash your car.Although we'd reserved for Sunday night as well we couldn't wait to get out early and find somewhere else, which we did and was 100% better, and less expensive as well.We've stayed here before but this was the last time. We've asked the staff each time we come there to tell us what the French parking signs say on the street and they refuse every time to translate them. The desk staff are rude and nasty, chamber maids were sweet and caring. The rooms are small and not worth a $100 stay per night by any means.I have travelled the world and this by far is the worst place I have ever stayed.	
Sep 26 2005	Good for the price but not in a safe area	My fiance and I stayed here to save a couple bucks rather than paying $150 a night to stay at a nicer hotel. If we could do it again, we'd pay the extra $$. There's no parking, and the lock on our room was broken. Now this made me feel a little insecure since on the cab ride there we witnessed two fights and a muggin right around the corner.Also, one of the nights we came back around midnight and there were two hookers sitting on the front steps smoking pot. No joke.One of our cab drivers said that there are alot of drug dealers in the area, so DO NOT go walking on the street late at night, for you are taking your life in your hands if you do.The room itself was clean and the staff was friendly, but the no parking and dangerous criminal activity in the area should be enough to keep you away.	
Sep 17 2005	I've stayed here three times have doubts if will again	Good points - I was there for the Champcar Racing Weekend in August. As this location is two subway stops from the race track and maybe 3 subway stops from Cresent street were all the festivities are, its a great location.The price is very reasonable all in $450 cdn for four nights.Problems/Issues - One the Saturday Night an older lady started knocking my door around 7:30pm. I ignored her, surprise to me she opened my door lucky i had the emergency keychain lock on. She sreamed open the door. I closed it and got dressed when I opened she had disappeared.On the sunday Night the cleaning staff left my door not closed properly...anyone could have walked in.Everyday and night from the Thursday to sunday there were teenage/twentish young people on the pay phone on the floor all the time. Also lots of banging of doors at all hours.Other issue is that around St. Laurent station south to St. Catherine the area did not seem nice. I have been there two other times and although there were cleanliness and other problems their, this time there were many more and more extreme. I would not recommend the hotel at all for families with children.Overall i'm not sure if I will return to this hotel. I love the location and price, but the problems in the hotel and the st. laurent station/st. catherine area are probably to much for me to return.	
Aug 31 2005	Filthy place	When we arrived at the hotel which by the way is part way down a hill, the only parking there was, was on the street. Garbage was strewn around the area - I actually asked the gentleman at the registration desk (who by the way was very friendly) if it was safe to leave our car out on the street all night.We arrived at the hotel around 6:00ish and were only able to stay the one night. Our thought was that 'hey it's only one night' how bad can it be.The room was absolutely filthy. On the floor beside the bed were beer caps - approx. 5. There was garbage behind the night table. The floors did appear to be vacuumed at least. When I went to take a bath, only the shower worked as there was no plug for the tub. There were two double beds in the room - first thing I checked was to see if the sheets were clean, and they were. If I happened to get up in the dark I would have smacked by knee on the dresser to get to the door as there was just no room to move around. No place to put luggage. The hallways did smell. The rooms were dark and dingy.Upon checking out the next morning registration desk asked how was your stay - I mentioned the state of the room and can quote her response of &quot;oh sorry!&quot; All of this for $100.00 a night!!!!!!!!The real unfortunate part of this whole story - I read the reviews for this hotel AFTER our trip. I am so sorry I did not take the time to read the reviews before.	
