Sep 29 2004	Best Avoided	I stayed at this hotel over a holiday weekend in September, and I don't think I've ever received such shoddy treatment from staff ever before.The individual rooms were nice, but that's where the niceness ends. The hallways, elevator and lobby area looked unkempt. A broken beer bottle sat in a stairwell for 2 days.The worst part of this hotel was its staff, who seemed to stoop to new lows in their quest to push guests out the door. I was checking out of the hotel on a holiday Monday, so it would be highly unlikely they were expecting a huge influx of guests the following day. But they seemed determined to push me out of the hotel A.S.A.P.Check-out time is 12 p.m. I left my room at 11:15 to get a coffee, and when I returned at 11:30 (the nearest coffee shop was about 15 minutes away - and I wasn't going to take a chance on the coffee in the lobby!), my electronic key card had been deactivated. Then, as I was finishing packing up and making sure I hadn't left anything behind, the front desk called to say &quot;Check-out time is 12.&quot; I felt like I was on some kind of assembly line. Believe me, at that point, I couldn't wait to get out of that dump.You may get a cheap rate at this hotel, but even though I'm a frugal traveller, I wouldn't stay here again.	
Aug 2 2004	Great Place	We were greeted by the manager, &quot;Jerry&quot; with a handshake and a warm welcome. Our internet reservation was ready to sign when we arrived. Jerry let us use his parking spot right outside the door. Our room on the main floor as requested, was clean and well appointed with a comfortable mattress and great shower being one of the best Econolodges we have stayed in. We were within a 10 minute walk to old Montreal. In the morning we had a continental breakfast with other apparently very satisfied travellers. It was an extremely pleasant stay and we would definitely stay here again. Thanks to Jerry and all staff for making our stay very enjoyable and convenient. P.S. Jerry, let me know that you got this message. Doug	
Jul 8 2004	Used to be ok now run down!	My husband &amp; I have stayed here numerous times, as we like the location (although it is on a very steep hill-not for the physically challenged) and the price. Unfortunately, over time the place has gotten rather run-down and grimy (hallways &amp; rooms), and seems ever-populated by swarms of young adults who like slamming doors in the wee hours. The price no longer seems worth the ick factor--and with so many other nice places to stay in Montreal (namely, b&amp;bs), we won't go back.	
